<h2>3 · Explain the Code 📖</h2>
<p>Read this working opening carefully. It asks for two variables, gives each a safe default, then prints one sentence.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">hero = game.ask(&quot;Hero's name?&quot;)
if hero == &quot;&quot;:
    hero = &quot;brave traveller&quot;

weapon = game.ask(&quot;Starting weapon?&quot;)
if weapon == &quot;&quot;:
    weapon = &quot;rusty sword&quot;

game.say(f&quot;{hero}, you grip your {weapon} and set out.&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What does the variable <code>hero</code> store after the player answers?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

